         <abstract>
            <p>The need to define appropriate costs of capital for different risk segments of a corporation's portfolio of businesses is recognized as an important issue in financial management. In practice, however, the problem of assessing multiple risk-adjusted hurdle rates may be particularly complex. Some suggestions are given on how to improve the estimation of divisional betas.</p>
